Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is attention mechanism?
AI Response

Attention allows a model to focus on relevant input parts during output generation. Self-attention in
transformers computes weighted relationships between all token pairs.

Example 1.2

User

What is the vanishing gradient problem?
AI Response

In deep networks, gradients shrink exponentially during backpropagation, preventing early layers from
learning. Solutions include ReLU activations, residual connections, and LSTMs.

Example 1.3

User

What is word embedding?
AI Response

Word embeddings map words to dense vectors where similar words are nearby. Word2Vec, GloVe, and
FastText are popular methods, used as NLP model input features.

Example 1.4

User

What is RLHF?
AI Response

Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback trains a reward model on human preference data, then uses
RL (PPO) to fine-tune an LLM to produce outputs humans prefer.

Example 1.5

User

What is the softmax function?
AI Response

Softmax converts a vector of raw scores (logits) into probabilities that sum to 1, typically used as the final
activation in multi-class classification models.

Example 1.6

User

What is an epoch?
AI Response

An epoch is one full pass through the entire training dataset. Multiple epochs are used, and the number is a
key hyperparameter affecting model convergence.

Example 1.7

User

What is mean squared error?
AI Response



MSE is (1/n) * sum of (predicted - actual)^2. It penalizes large errors heavily and is a standard loss function
for regression tasks, sensitive to outliers.

Example 1.8

User

What is GPT?
AI Response

GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) is an autoregressive language model trained to predict the next
token. GPT-3 and GPT-4 are large-scale versions capable of diverse language tasks.

Example 1.9

User

What is backpropagation?
AI Response

Backpropagation computes gradients of the loss with respect to each weight by applying the chain rule
backwards through the network, enabling weight updates via gradient descent.

Example 1.10

User

What is K-means clustering?
AI Response

K-means partitions data into K clusters by iteratively assigning points to the nearest centroid and updating
centroids as the mean of assigned points, minimizing intra-cluster variance.



